OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FMainly dry start, with sunny
OL,6,Fspells. However, cloud soon thickening
OL,7,Ffrom the west, with winds also
OL,8,Fstrengthening. Likely staying dry for
OL,9,Fmost, but some light rain moving into
OL,10,Fnorthwestern parts from late afternoon.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FRain and drizzle will become
OL,13,Fwidespread through the evening, mostly
OL,14,Flight but with some heavier bursts
OL,15,Fpossible. Maybe the odd drier spell
OL,16,Fdeveloping towards dawn. Winds also
OL,17,Feasing. Mild.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
